    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-11-01T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-11-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="426"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d426">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/11–148: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Mukden</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ward</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mukden</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-11-01">November 1,
                            1948</date>.<lb/>[Received November 1—3:23 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>474. 1510 hours Communist troops now in effective occupation of Mukden. Small
                    arms fire which has been going on within city since daylight has ceased.</p>
                <p>Sent Nanking 619; repeated Department 474, Peiping 245, Tientsin 161, Tsingtao
                    123.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Ward</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
